news.title: China's first publicly traded rental property REITs snapped up by investors
news.para: The REITs will raise a combined 3.8 billion yuan ($56 million), based on Reuters' calculations, and the subscription periods ended early.

news.title: Two years on, Ahmedabad to expand again
news.para: The now cash-strapped Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation (AMC) is promising a single village, Nandoli, in Kalol taluka of Gandhinagar district, modern infrastructure after inclusion in municipal limits.

news.title: High court directs Goa government to verify reports of illegal sand mining
news.para: The network also submitted to the court a picture frontpaged by TOI on Wednesday showing large heaps of illegally mined sand ready for transportation on the banks of the Mandovi in Naroa, Bicholim.

news.title: Home sale deeds registration jump 124% year-on-year in Kolkata in July 2022
news.para: ​With the extended incentive period due to get over this September, realtors and developers expect the high sales to continue and result in even more registrations at the state directorate of registrations and stamps revenue.

news.title: Delhi civic body attaches three commercial properties in west zone over tax default
news.para: Two properties -- Anand Vatika and Sonam Vatika -- situated on the main road in Bapraula did not pay property tax from 2004. Similarly, a property at Chanakya Place Part-1, Uttam Nagar, had total accumulated dues of Rs 16,93,440, excluding interest and penalty, the statement said.

news.title: Government permits Nashik civic body to use AutoDCR software for online approval
news.para: At present, the NMC uses the BPMS software — provided by the state government — for online submission and approval of the building plans. But the builders face some technical issues with the submission and approval of the plans.

news.title: Visakhapatnam: Few more vacant lands put on auction
news.para: The authorities are expecting more than Rs 300 crores to Rs 400 crores which can be deposited into the state government’s exchequer.

news.title: American Balanced Fund offloads 2.9 crore shares of Embassy Office Parks REIT worth Rs 1,046 crore
news.para: The shares were disposed of at an average price of Rs 357.61 apiece, taking the transaction size to Rs 1,046.45 crore.

news.title: One of Supertech twin towers fully rigged with explosives, work in full swing on other
news.para: The nearly 100-metre tall structures are scheduled for demolition at 2.30 pm on August 28 in pursuance of a Supreme Court order that found the twin towers in Sector 93A were built in violation of norms.

news.title: Government may order mandatory redevelopment of Delhi areas
news.para: The proposed changes may cause a stir since the urban regeneration scheme has been given a wide ambit. It could be applied to developed areas or vacant or lal dora land of an urbanised village.

news.title: Bombay HC slams BMC for occupation certificate to buildings with no water
news.para: The interim direction came on a petition by Subodh Joshi, resident of an old building at Kirol village in Ghatkopar that was demolished in 2011 and redeveloped.

news.title: Only 54 societies give consent for multi-point meters in Greater Noida
news.para: In Shivalik Homes near Surajpur, for instance, NPCL organised an awareness camp for multi-point meter connections in the society earlier this week.

news.title: Odisha government asks urban bodies to ready disaster management plan
news.para: There have been an increase in natural disasters due to climate change affecting people, infrastructure and assets in urban areas.

news.title: After Punjab & Haryana HC intervention, HSVP allottee hopes to get plot after 30 years
news.para: Bansal was 38 years old when he was allotted the plot in 1992, but he could not get possession of the plot even when he turned 68 years old.

news.title: Kolkata civic body to issue certificates for tenants before razing unsafe buildings
news.para: In an attempt to address the insecurity among a section of tenants living in unsafe buildings across the city, the Kolkata Municipal Corporation has decided to issue certificates recording the names of tenants before the civic body decides to demolish dilapidated buildings on the grounds of public safety.
